16
Subtitle
17
18 TO CLARIFY THE DEFINITION OF "PRINCIPAL
19 OFFICE" USED UNDER THE ARKANSAS BUSINESS
20 CORPORATION ACT OF 1987 AND THE UNIFORM
21 LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY ACT.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 4-27-140(17), concerning the definition of
26 "principal office" used under the Arkansas Business Corporation Act of 1987,
27 is amended to read as follows:
28 (17)(A) "Principal office" means the office (in or out of this state)
29 so designated in the annual franchise tax report where the principal
30 executive offices of a domestic or foreign corporation are located.
31 (B) If the domestic or foreign corporation does not have a
32 "principal office" as described under subdivision (17)(A) of this section,
33 the domestic or foreign corporation may designate the address of the domestic
34 or foreign corporation's registered agent as the principal office of the
35 domestic or foreign corporation.
36 (C) A domestic or foreign corporation listing the address
