1 of its registered agent under subdivision (17)(B) of this section shall
2 provide the Secretary of State with the physical address of a named officer
3 or director.
4
5 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code ยง 4-38-102(16), concerning the definition of
6 "principal office" used under the Uniform Limited Liability Company Act, is
7 amended to read as follows:
8 (16)(A) "Principal office" means the principal executive office
9 of a limited liability company or foreign limited liability company, whether
10 or not the office is located in this state.
11 (B) If the limited liability company or foreign limited
12 liability company does not have a "principal office" as described under
13 subdivision (16)(A) of this section, the limited liability company or foreign
14 limited liability company may designate the address of the limited liability
15 company or foreign limited liability company's registered agent as the
16 principal office of the limited liability company or foreign limited
17 liability company.
18 (C) A limited liability company or foreign limited
19 liability company listing the address of its registered agent under
20 subdivision (16)(B) of this section shall provide the Secretary of State with
21 the physical address of a named member or manager.
